title: VIDEO: Thursday Night High School Football
text:
VIDEO: Thursday Night High School Football 
By Norman Seawright III October 8, 2015 Updated Oct 8, 2015 at 10:37 PM CDT 
(NNCNOW.com) -- The final regular season week of Minnesota State High School League (MSHSL) football kicked off with Thursday night games, headlined by No. 5 Hermantown's win over Moose Lake-Willow River. 
After defeating the Rebels 59-35, the Hawks complete an undefeated season moving into the postseason.
